  "why": "The paper's evaluation focuses exclusively on the efficiency and effectiveness of the proposed testing method, BET, in discovering failures. It uses metrics such as the number of error-inducing inputs (Err-Num), the number of unique misclassified labels (Label-Num), and the success rate (SR) to compare its performance against other methods. While these metrics quantify the outcome of the testing process, the paper does not use them to provide any diagnostic insight into why the models fail. There is no analysis linking the discovered failures to underlying model vulnerabilities, model internals, or even statistical failure patterns beyond simply counting the diversity of wrong labels. The paper reports the quantity and diversity of failures as a measure of the fuzzer's performance, rather than as a means to diagnose the model's weaknesses. The discussion section explicitly identifies the need for new metrics to understand the model's internal state in a black-box setting as a future research direction, confirming the absence of such diagnostics in the current work.",
